---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/base-layout.astro";
import SiteHeader from "@components/site-header.astro";

const title = "About";
const description = "About - Programs Fall Apart";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <main id="main-content">
    <SiteHeader />
    <section>
      <div>
        <p>Hey there, I’m Amira (ah-mee-rah).</p>
        <p>
          I started off in mathematics, but somewhere along the way, I stumbled into software engineering and just stayed. 
        </p>

        <p>
          I’m not here to claim mastery over anything. I’m just a curious
          programmer with a skeptical mind. This blog comes from those
          nights, you know, when a "quick fix" spirals into a three-hour deep
          dive on why programming languages handle whitespace differently, all
          while a forgotten coffee cup grows cold beside you. That’s where
          most of these posts come from.
        </p>

        <p>
          This is a space for learning, not to be taken too seriously.
          I’m here to share the journey, probably mess up a few times, and maybe
          even spark some real conversations. If you ever feel like reaching
          out, I’m just a comment, an <a
            href="mailto:amira@programsfallapart.com"
            >email</a
          >, or <a
            href="https://twitter.com/pfa_amira"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >twitter <span class="sr-only">(opens in new tab)</span></a
          > away. Let’s see where this rabbit hole goes.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
